16 SECTION 1.
17 Part 14 of Article 6 of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
18 relating to other educational programs under the "Quality Basic Education Act," is amended
19 by revising Code Section 20-2-310, relating to student directory information, registering to
20 vote and with selective service, and pledge of allegiance, as follows:
21 "20-2-310.
22 (a) Any local school system or public school at the secondary level which provides access
23 to the campus school property or to student directory information to persons or groups
24 which make students aware of occupational or educational options shall provide access to
25 the campus school property and student directory information on at least the same basis to
26 official recruiting representatives of the military forces of the state and the United States
27 for the purpose of informing students of educational and career opportunities available in
28 the military.
29 (b) No local school system, public school, or any person acting on behalf of a local school
30 system or public school shall disclose or otherwise provide access to student directory
31 information to any candidate or campaign committee, as such terms are defined in Code
32 Section 21-5-3, any political action committee or political organization, as such terms are
33 defined in Code Section 21-5-30.2, or any person or group acting on behalf of such
34 candidate, campaign committee, political action committee, or political organization.
35 (c) Each eligible student in the public schools of this state shall be apprised of his or her
36 right to register as an elector and to vote in elections and of any obligation to register with
37 the Selective Service System. Each eligible student shall be given an opportunity, arranged
38 by the school administration, to register to vote at his or her school during the month of
39 April of each year. The State Board of Education shall promulgate rules and regulations
40 to carry out this Code section. An excused absence of a student to register or vote, at the
41 discretion of the local unit of administration, shall not exceed one school day.
