42 (d) Each person who, while located on public school property in this state, apprises one
43 or more public school students of their right to register as an elector and to vote in elections
44 or of their obligation to register with the Selective Service System or who arranges for or
45 assists one or more public school students to register to vote shall attest in writing that he
46 or she is not acting directly or indirectly on behalf of and will not provide any student
47 directory information to any candidate or campaign committee, as such terms are defined
48 in Code Section 21-5-3, any political action committee or political organization, as such
49 terms are defined in Code Section 21-5-30.2, or any person or group acting on behalf of
50 such candidate, campaign committee, political action committee, or political organization.
51 The requirements of this subsection shall not apply to a public school administrator,
52 teacher, or other school personnel while engaged in the performance of official duties.
53 (c)(e)(1) Each student in the public schools of this state shall be afforded the opportunity
54 to recite the Pledge of Allegiance to the flag of the United States of America during each
55 school day. It shall be the duty of each local board of education to establish a policy
56 setting the time and manner for recitation of the Pledge of Allegiance. Such policy shall
57 be established in writing and shall be distributed to each teacher within the school.
58 (2) The State School Superintendent shall prepare for the use of the public schools of this
59 state a program of instruction, subject to the approval of the State Board of Education,
60 in the correct use and display of the flag of the United States of America which shall
61 include, as a minimum, specific instruction regarding respect for such flag and its display
62 and use as provided by federal law and regulation, and under such regulations and
63 instructions as may best meet the varied requirements of the different grades in such
64 schools. However, such instruction shall include, as a minimum, the provisions of 36
65 U.S.C. Sections 170 through 177.
66 (f) The State Board of Education shall promulgate rules and regulations to carry out this
67 Code section."
