68 SECTION 2.
69 Article 15 of Chapter 2 of Title 21 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
70 miscellaneous offenses relating to elections and primaries, is amended by revising Code
71 Section 21-2-561, relating to false registration, as follows:
72 "21-2-561.
73 Any person who:
74 (1) Registers as an elector knowing that such elector does not possess the qualifications
75 required by law;
76 (2) Registers as an elector under any other name than the elector's own name; or
77 (3) Knowingly gives false information when registering as an elector; or
78 (4) Discloses to an unauthorized person any information that is exempted from public
79 inspection pursuant to Code Section 21-2-225 or is confidential pursuant to Code
80 Section 21-2-225.1
81 shall be guilty of a felony and, upon conviction thereof, shall be sentenced to imprisonment
82 for not less than one nor more than ten years or to pay a fine not to exceed $100,000.00,
83 or both."
84 SECTION 3.
85 Article 1 of Chapter 5 of Title 21 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
86 general provisions for government transparency and campaign finance, is amended by adding
87 a new Code section to read as follows:
88 "21-5-16.
89 No candidate, campaign committee, or political action committee shall solicit any
90 individual under the age of 18 years to fraudulently organize an event on the property of
91 any local school system when the purpose of such event is influencing the nomination for
92 election or election of any person for office, bringing about the recall of a public officer
93 holding elective office or opposing the recall of a public officer holding elective office, or
